In this press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney discusses a range of topics. He talks about the President's nominee for the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) and emphasizes her experience in health care policy. Carney also addresses concerns about the nominee's confirmation hearings and the potential for them to devolve into a fight about the merits of the Affordable Care Act. He also discusses the recent passing of the Iran envoy bill and the President's decision not to issue a visa to the Iranian ambassador to the UN. Carney mentions that the President's trip to New York is for personal reasons, and he briefly discusses voting rights, the situation in Ukraine, and Guantanamo Bay. Finally, Carney mentions the President's upcoming speeches at the National Action Network and the Easter Prayer Breakfast.